Since $f(z)$ is equidistant from $z$ and the origin, $|f(z) - z| = |f(z)|.$  Then
\[|(a + bi)z - z| = |(a + bi)z|.\]Dividing both sides by $|z|,$ we get
\[|(a + bi) - 1| = |a + bi|.\]Since $|a + bi| = 8,$ this reduces to $|(a - 1) + bi| = 8.$

